Naledi Shange, News24(File, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A man who allegedly tried to rob a woman was killed in a mob justice attack in Pretoria West on Friday morning, police said.&nbsp;Police found the man, in his 20s, in a pool of his own blood with injuries to his upper body, Constable Tumisang Moloto said.&nbsp;Locals caught him when he tried to rob the woman and allegedly beat him to death. Sticks and other weapons were found next to his corpse.His identity was not yet known and no arrests had been made. Police called for anyone with information about his killers to come forward.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.